body: Good DD I have had a position in Trimble for a number of years as I use their products everyday ( surveyor) I love the company and will keep accumulating!

author: Alternative_Row_9645
body: Trimble is ubiquitous in the construction industry.  Every major company I have ever worked for uses Trimble products/software.

author: ixikei
body:
I work in civil engineering and have noticed that LiDAR seems to be eliminating the need for traditional topographic surveys (and Trimble provides a ton of traditional surveying equipment!). 

Does that basic thesis agree with what you've noticed? Do you think Trimble is a good play for the change in surveying methodology, or would you recommend a different company?

author: LegHam2021
body: Trimble I believe will always be apart of the process. The thing with the LiDAR is that you set up on known coordinates calculated traditionally using theodolite and now more often than not GPS survey equipment. But that is just one small part of their business I also work in the mining industry and they have a large part of the mining machine guidance and control. And as the trucks become more autonomous I think Trimble will be there as to play a large part.

Baidu | Fanuc Corporation | CrowdStrike Holdings | 3D Systems Corporation | Tesla
iRobot | Nvidia | ZScaler | Stratasys Ltd. | Baidu
Veracyte | ABB Ltd. | Twilio | iRobot | Materialise NV Sponsored ADR
Varonis Systems | Keyence Corporation | Datadog | AeroVironment, Inc. | Trimble Inc
MongoDB | Intuitive Surgical | Varonis Systems | FLIR Systems, Inc. | Deere & Company
Tencent | Renishaw plc | First American Funds Inc X Treasury Obligations Fund | HIWIN Technologies Corp. | JD.com, Inc. Sponsored ADR Class A
Twilio | Brooks Automation | Unity Software | Vocera Communications, Inc. | Google/Alphabet
Illumina | Yaskawa Electric Corporation | Guardant Health | Illumina | Kratos Defense & Security Solutions, Inc.	
Nuance Communications | Daifuku Co., Ltd. | Elastic NV | Manhattan Associates, Inc. | Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing 
MSFT | Tecan Group AG | Okta Inc. | Krones AG | Nano Dimension Ltd Sponsored ADR


There's almost no common themes! iRobot, Twilio, Illumina appear twice, that's about it.

And so many of these are companies I've never heard of, but are geographically spread out, leaders in their respective industries and sound very very promising, e.g.:

> FLIR Systems is the world's largest commercial company specializing in the design and production of thermal imaging cameras, components and imaging sensors.

> JD.com, Inc., also known as Jingdong and formerly called 360buy, is a Chinese e-commerce company headquartered in Beijing. It is one of the two massive B2C online retailers in China by transaction volume and revenue, a member of the Fortune Global 500 and a major competitor to Alibaba-run Tmall.

>Tecan Group Ltd. is a Swiss company providing laboratory instruments and solutions in biopharmaceuticals, forensics, and clinical diagnostics for pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies, university research departments and diagnostic laboratories. 

>Daifuku Co., Ltd. is a Japanese material-handling equipment company, founded in 1937, in Osaka. As of 2017 it was the leading material handling system supplier in the world.

>Veracyte develops molecular tests for oncology. The Company offers molecular cytology and tests for the diagnostic accuracy of cytology samples. Veracyte provides its products and services to healthcare and molecular diagnostic companies in the United States. 

I suppose can't really go wrong with one, but I think i'll pick at least two.

author: how_you_feel
body:
So I did some DD here and wanted to get back to you, because they don't seem to have the same holdings at all!

I took 5 AI/Robotics/Industrial innovation ETFs and looked at the top 10 holdings:


THNQ | BOTZ | LRNZ | ROBO  | ARKQ
---|---|----|----|----
Baidu | Fanuc Corporation | CrowdStrike Holdings | 3D Systems Corporation | Tesla
iRobot | Nvidia | ZScaler | Stratasys Ltd. | Baidu
Veracyte | ABB Ltd. | Twilio | iRobot | Materialise NV Sponsored ADR
Varonis Systems | Keyence Corporation | Datadog | AeroVironment, Inc. | Trimble Inc
MongoDB | Intuitive Surgical | Varonis Systems | FLIR Systems, Inc. | Deere & Company
Tencent | Renishaw plc | First American Funds Inc X Treasury Obligations Fund | HIWIN Technologies Corp. | JD.com, Inc. Sponsored ADR Class A
Twilio | Brooks Automation | Unity Software | Vocera Communications, Inc. | Google/Alphabet
Illumina | Yaskawa Electric Corporation | Guardant Health | Illumina | Kratos Defense & Security Solutions, Inc.	
Nuance Communications | Daifuku Co., Ltd. | Elastic NV | Manhattan Associates, Inc. | Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing 
MSFT | Tecan Group AG | Okta Inc. | Krones AG | Nano Dimension Ltd Sponsored ADR


There's almost no common themes! iRobot, Twilio, Illumina appear twice, that's about it.

And so many of these are companies I've never heard of, but are geographically spread out, leaders in their respective industries and sound very very promising, e.g.:

> FLIR Systems is the world's largest commercial company specializing in the design and production of thermal imaging cameras, components and imaging sensors.

> JD.com, Inc., also known as Jingdong and formerly called 360buy, is a Chinese e-commerce company headquartered in Beijing. It is one of the two massive B2C online retailers in China by transaction volume and revenue, a member of the Fortune Global 500 and a major competitor to Alibaba-run Tmall.

>Tecan Group Ltd. is a Swiss company providing laboratory instruments and solutions in biopharmaceuticals, forensics, and clinical diagnostics for pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies, university research departments and diagnostic laboratories. 

>Daifuku Co., Ltd. is a Japanese material-handling equipment company, founded in 1937, in Osaka. As of 2017 it was the leading material handling system supplier in the world.

>Veracyte develops molecular tests for oncology. The Company offers molecular cytology and tests for the diagnostic accuracy of cytology samples. Veracyte provides its products and services to healthcare and molecular diagnostic companies in the United States.
